  "bio": [
    "Wang Xinyang is the founder, chairman and CEO of state-backed Gpixel Changchun Microelectronics, a fabless maker of CMOS image sensors - chips that turn incoming light into digital images.",
    "Before setting up Gpixel in 2012, UK- and Dutch-educated Wang worked with CMOSIS NV, a Belgian company in CMOS image sensor design.",
    "He also worked as a researcher and Ph.D. supervisor at the Changchun Institute of Optics, Fine Mechanics and Physics.",
    "Wang took Gpixel public on the Hong Kong stock exchange in April 2026, raising $332 million.",
    "His wife, Zhang Yanxia, serves as Gpixel's deputy general manager."
